[
  {
    "text": "Starting with tvOS 11.2, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple TV 4K can automatically switch video display modes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "to match the native frame rate and dynamic range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "of video content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Video and Audio section of the Settings app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "allows the matching frame rate and dynamic range behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be set independently, and enables viewing of content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "it its original frame rate and dynamic range. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "By default, these options are disabled. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "When enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "and video content is played back in a compatible app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "tvOS will automatically switch the video display settings ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "to match that of the content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "For instance, if the content is in 24 frames per second ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "and standard dynamic range, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "the device will switch from its system mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "to 24 frame per second, standard dynamic range mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once the media playback session is over, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "the device will then switch back to its system mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first step in supporting frame rate matching ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your content is to ensure that your HLS master playlists ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "are fully annotated with the native frame rate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the variants using the FRAME-RATE attribute. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "If a playlist does not include the FRAME-RATE attribute, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=70"
  },
  {
    "text": "frame rate mode switching will not be supported ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "for that asset. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "Furthermore, only playlists that declare ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=76"
  },
  {
    "text": "either a single frame rate for all variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=79"
  },
  {
    "text": "or only have frame rates ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are integer multiples of the smallest frame rate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "are supported. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, 29.97 and 59.94.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dynamic range mode matching ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "does not typically require any changes to your playlists, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "as content is assumed to be SDR ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=98"
  },
  {
    "text": "unless the VIDEO-RANGE attribute specifies otherwise, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "as all non-SDR content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "must include the VIDEO-RANGE attribute already.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=104"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apps that use AVPlayerViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "will automatically support mode matching, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=111"
  },
  {
    "text": "unless the appliesPreferred DisplayCriteriaAutomatically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "property is changed to false.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "When content is played back in full screen ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "using AVPlayerViewController, tvOS will automatically switch ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the appropriate display mode for that content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, when AVPlayerViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "leaves full-screen mode or is dismissed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "tvOS will switch back to its system display mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "For apps that play back full-screen content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "using AVPlayerViewController or TVMLKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "no additional work is required. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=143"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, for other scenarios where your video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "might not always be played back in full screen, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you are playing multiple videos simultaneously, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "switching between different short videos frequently, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=155"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you aren't using AVPlayerViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your video playback, you may need to directly specify ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "the AVDisplayManager preferredDisplayCriteria ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "to ensure that the mode switch occurs at the right time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "and reflects the characteristics ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the appropriate media content.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you are using AVPlayerViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "and wish to opt out of mode switching entirely ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "or need to manage the display mode manually, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "begin by setting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "the appliesPreferredDisplay CriteriaAutomatically property ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "of AVPlayerViewController to false. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will disable the automatic AVKit matching behavior. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, to trigger tvOS to switch modes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "to match a specific piece of content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "retrieve the AVDisplayCriteria object vended by ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "the preferredDisplayCriteria property of the AVAsset. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "Assign that AVDisplayCriteria object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the preferredDisplayCriteria property ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the AVDisplayManager vended by the key UIWindow. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "The mode switch will occur upon setting this property, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "assuming that matching was enabled in settings ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=221"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that the attached device supports the preferred mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "You should perform this switch before assigning ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=228"
  },
  {
    "text": "the AVPlayerItem to the AVPlayer object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=230"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that AVPlayer configures itself ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "based on the targeted display mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "To switch back to the system's default mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=238"
  },
  {
    "text": "simply set the preferredDisplayCriteria ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "property to nil.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "To know when the mode switch begins and ends, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can key-value observe ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "the displayModeSwitchInProgress property ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the AVDisplayManager object. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help you determine the best way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "to make use of this new feature in your media application, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "here are some guidelines to keep in mind: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=259"
  },
  {
    "text": "Switch modes only as often as necessary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "All televisions respond to mode switching a little differently, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "but it will generally cause the screen to flash ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "or temporarily black out, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "and may take a few seconds to complete. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "This can be disruptive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "if it occurs more often than necessary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "Typically, mode switching ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "is only appropriate for full-screen playback. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=281"
  },
  {
    "text": "Matching frame rate and dynamic range for content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "that plays in the background, as a thumbnail, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "or as an interstitial as part of a game, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be quite disruptive and is generally unnecessary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "The primary user interface of your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "outside of the video viewing experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "should be run in the system's frame rate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that UI and animations are smooth and fluid. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the television is in a lower frame rate mode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "those animations and movements ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "will also render at that frame rate, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "and may appear less smooth as a result.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are also several circumstances ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "where leaving the device in its system mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "will yield an improved user experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app plays shorter clips, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "displays multiple video tiles simultaneously, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=328"
  },
  {
    "text": "or frequently switches between content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "with disparate characteristics, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "it would be preferred to avoid mode switching entirely ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "to ensure the viewing experience is not disrupted unnecessarily.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "tvOS 11.2 enables video content frame rate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "and dynamic range matching on Apple TV 4K. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "AVPlayerViewController ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=353"
  },
  {
    "text": "can manage this behavior automatically, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "but some apps will want more control ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "by utilizing AVDisplayManager and AVDisplayCriteria.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=359"
  },
  {
    "text": "Please visit developer.apple.com\nfor more information.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-503/?time=365"
  }
]